1
00:00:02,468 --> 00:00:04,969
[ Ukulele Strumming ]

2
00:00:23,088 --> 00:00:23,588
Phew. Wow.

3
00:00:23,590 --> 00:00:25,256
I thought last year's
Art Crawl was terrible,

4
00:00:25,258 --> 00:00:27,558
but they really outdid
themselves this year, huh?

5
00:00:27,560 --> 00:00:29,694
[ Louise ]
Yeah.
Ugh, bad.

6
00:00:29,696 --> 00:00:30,461
Very bad.
Mm-hmm.

7
00:00:30,463 --> 00:00:32,597
Oh, look at that.
Really bad.
[ Gags ]

8
00:00:32,599 --> 00:00:36,234
Really, really bad.
I think they're...
good.

9
00:00:36,236 --> 00:00:38,136
Dad, why does Art Crawl
suck so much?

10
00:00:38,138 --> 00:00:43,474
Well, it's just a very loose
definition of art, Louise.
And don't say "suck."

11
00:00:43,476 --> 00:00:45,276
Don't say "suck," please.

12
00:00:45,278 --> 00:00:46,577
You're right though.
It does suck.

13
00:00:46,579 --> 00:00:49,547
I don't want you kids to think
this is what art is.

14
00:00:49,549 --> 00:00:50,715
We should go
to a museum.

15
00:00:50,717 --> 00:00:52,450
Whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa.
Yeah, maybe not.

16
00:00:52,452 --> 00:00:54,085
We should not
go to a museum.
Let's not overdo it.

17
00:00:54,087 --> 00:00:58,189
Let's just walk around
and make fun of this stuff.
[ Gene ] Yeah.

18
00:00:58,191 --> 00:00:59,724
Why don't we just go back
to the restaurant?

19
00:00:59,726 --> 00:01:02,560
Because your Aunt Gayle is there
hanging up her art,

20
00:01:02,562 --> 00:01:04,228
which we're not allowed
to make fun of at all.

21
00:01:04,230 --> 00:01:07,432
Well, why can't we make fun
of Aunt Gayle's paintings?

22
00:01:07,434 --> 00:01:08,766
She's family.
Yeah.

23
00:01:08,768 --> 00:01:11,769
That means never
holding back anything.
Right, pit stains?

24
00:01:11,771 --> 00:01:15,907
Am I showing?
Let's just say your shirt looks
like my underwear right now.

25
00:01:15,909 --> 00:01:19,310
Yeah. Well, look,
no one tells Gayle
anything she can't handle.

26
00:01:19,312 --> 00:01:22,313
That's your mom's rule.
You treat her like
a mental patient.

27
00:01:22,315 --> 00:01:24,882
Well, I mean, she probably
should be one, right?

28
00:01:24,884 --> 00:01:27,452
Yeah, I heard she ate
her lipstick once...

29
00:01:27,454 --> 00:01:29,220
because she wanted
to feel "red" inside.

30
00:01:29,222 --> 00:01:32,657
And she made a dress
out of "live shrimp"
and wore it to Mass.

31
00:01:32,659 --> 00:01:36,527
- Oh, and she shaved her cat.
- Louise, you know
none of that is true.

32
00:01:36,529 --> 00:01:38,196
Except for the cat shaving.

33
00:01:38,198 --> 00:01:40,164
Maybe the shrimp
and the lipstick.

34
00:01:40,166 --> 00:01:42,733
Are you kidding me?
My kid could paint that.

35
00:01:42,735 --> 00:01:44,902
[ Tina ]
Wow. It costs $200.

36
00:01:44,904 --> 00:01:46,537
Someone bought that mess?

37
00:01:46,539 --> 00:01:48,873
How rude!
Harold!
[ Snoring ]

38
00:01:48,875 --> 00:01:49,674
Harold!
What?

39
00:01:49,676 --> 00:01:53,277
There are some
poorly supervised
children amongst the art.

40
00:01:53,279 --> 00:01:54,879
Get rid of them!
All right.

41
00:01:54,881 --> 00:01:56,347
Let's go.
Keep moving.

42
00:01:56,349 --> 00:01:58,282
Excuse me. Are you a--
Are you a bouncer?

43
00:01:58,284 --> 00:02:00,318
Are you gonna
bounce my kids?
No, no.

44
00:02:00,320 --> 00:02:02,386
- Just keep it moving, chubs.
- Chubs?

45
00:02:02,388 --> 00:02:04,622
You don't have to go home,
but you can't stay here.

46
00:02:04,624 --> 00:02:06,390
[ Coughs, Wheezes ]
Hey, easy, pal.
All right?

47
00:02:06,392 --> 00:02:09,393
Don't touch.
Come on, Dad.
This guy's not worth it.

48
00:02:09,395 --> 00:02:11,963
- Listen to your kids, fatsy.
- Fatsy?

49
00:02:11,965 --> 00:02:14,232
Come on, Dad.
Dad, look me--
Louise--

50
00:02:14,234 --> 00:02:16,134
Give me your eyes, Dad.
Give me your eyes.
Mm-hmm.

51
00:02:16,136 --> 00:02:18,836
Take a deep breath.
You are lucky, pal!

52
00:02:18,838 --> 00:02:19,637
It's not worth it, Dad.

53
00:02:19,639 --> 00:02:23,341
If you hit him, your hand would
smell like ointment and pee.

54
00:02:23,343 --> 00:02:25,042
You smell
like ointment and pee.

55
00:02:25,044 --> 00:02:27,011
You smell
like ointment and pee!

56
00:02:27,013 --> 00:02:28,713
You smell
like ointment and pee!

57
00:02:28,715 --> 00:02:31,616
You smell
like ointment and pee!
You--

58
00:02:33,685 --> 00:02:35,920
Well, that was awkward.
What is that place?

59
00:02:35,922 --> 00:02:36,954
You don't know
Reflections?

60
00:02:36,956 --> 00:02:41,626
They sell art, not just during
Art Crawl, but year-round.

61
00:02:41,628 --> 00:02:42,293
Reflections.

62
00:02:42,295 --> 00:02:44,595
Sounds like a strip club
the way you say it.

63
00:02:44,597 --> 00:02:46,264
Reflections.
Mmm!

64
00:02:46,266 --> 00:02:48,599
So, brace yourselves
for Aunt Gayle's art show.

65
00:02:48,601 --> 00:02:51,802
Mom said Aunt Gayle told her
they're just adorable animals.

66
00:02:51,804 --> 00:02:53,971
Oh, yeah? Well, that
doesn't sound so bad.

67
00:02:53,973 --> 00:02:56,440
H-H-Hi, hon!
How was Art Crawl?
Hey.

68
00:02:56,442 --> 00:02:59,544
Huh? Everything's
going great here.
We're having fun.

69
00:02:59,546 --> 00:03:00,811
- Oh, wow.
- Lin--

70
00:03:00,813 --> 00:03:02,780
Gayle's here.
We h-h-hung her paintings.

71
00:03:02,782 --> 00:03:04,782
Look at this one!
Look at that one!

72
00:03:04,784 --> 00:03:09,187
Linda, can you
just let me see--
Oh, my God!

73
00:03:10,322 --> 00:03:12,790
Yeah!
Anuses!

74
00:03:14,426 --> 00:03:16,694
Oh, God.
Oh, my God, Lin.

75
00:03:16,696 --> 00:03:17,595
It's a few days, Bobby.

76
00:03:17,597 --> 00:03:20,331
Linda, there are animal anuses
all over our walls.

77
00:03:20,333 --> 00:03:23,501
Just think of 'em
as cute little rumps.
Lin, they're anuses.

78
00:03:23,503 --> 00:03:27,004
I'm trying to think
of worse paintings
to hang in a restaurant.

79
00:03:27,006 --> 00:03:29,273
Um-- Nope.
I can't think of any.

80
00:03:29,275 --> 00:03:31,309
- Bad monkey!
- Kids, stop that.

81
00:03:31,311 --> 00:03:32,643
No. I'm spanking
the monkey!

82
00:03:32,645 --> 00:03:37,315
No way, Dad.
This is the best thing
that has ever happened to us.

83
00:03:37,317 --> 00:03:37,715
Horse butt.

84
00:03:37,717 --> 00:03:40,718
Oh, hello, sir. Don't look
at the pictures of the anus--

85
00:03:40,720 --> 00:03:41,586
Oh, he already did.
Okay.

86
00:03:41,588 --> 00:03:44,555
You see that, Lin?
No one wants to eat with
one of those staring at them.

87
00:03:44,557 --> 00:03:47,992
Come on, you can't seriously
think that this is a good idea.

88
00:03:47,994 --> 00:03:48,893
Well, they're not for me,

89
00:03:48,895 --> 00:03:52,463
but we promised Gayle
she could display her art
for the Art Crawl.

90
00:03:52,465 --> 00:03:54,298
We can't take it back now.
She's fragile.

91
00:03:54,300 --> 00:03:57,401
- We have to support her.
- She's not that fragile, Lin.

92
00:03:57,403 --> 00:03:59,804
[ Fork Clinks ]
Oh!
[ Hyperventilating ]

93
00:03:59,806 --> 00:04:00,838
What happened?
What happened?

94
00:04:00,840 --> 00:04:03,608
Gayle, Gayle honey, look.
Look, it's a fork.

95
00:04:03,610 --> 00:04:05,776
[ Whimpering ]
What?
Look, it's a fork.

96
00:04:05,778 --> 00:04:06,677
Oh, it's a fork. Heh.

97
00:04:06,679 --> 00:04:10,381
Oh, you're killing me.
She's killing me.
[ Chuckling ]

98
00:04:10,383 --> 00:04:11,549
Okay, so she's fragile.

99
00:04:11,551 --> 00:04:13,884
And that means we have
to be the anus restaurant?

100
00:04:13,886 --> 00:04:15,453
Yes, it means that.

101
00:04:15,455 --> 00:04:16,687
Oh, we can make T-shirts!

102
00:04:16,689 --> 00:04:19,357
It'll say:
"Milk, milk, lemonade.

103
00:04:19,359 --> 00:04:21,926
Around the corner,
art is made."

104
00:04:21,928 --> 00:04:23,894
Bob! Do you love 'em?

105
00:04:23,896 --> 00:04:25,630
Or do you
just love 'em?

106
00:04:25,632 --> 00:04:27,431
Um, how did you--

107
00:04:27,433 --> 00:04:30,334
Why-- Why would you paint--
this?

108
00:04:30,336 --> 00:04:34,605
The inspiration came to me
on a mountaintop.

109
00:04:34,607 --> 00:04:37,408
What should I paint?

110
00:04:37,410 --> 00:04:39,043
[ Creature Chittering ]

111
00:04:39,045 --> 00:04:40,811
[ Chittering ]

112
00:04:40,813 --> 00:04:45,716
[ Gayle's Voice ]
♪ I look at you
I see in you ♪

113
00:04:45,718 --> 00:04:49,787
♪ I see what's inside you

114
00:04:49,789 --> 00:04:53,391
Huh.
He loves 'em!

115
00:04:57,396 --> 00:04:58,095
All right, listen up.

116
00:04:58,097 --> 00:05:00,464
All the suckers
come out for Art Crawl.

117
00:05:00,466 --> 00:05:02,667
And they all want
to pay money for crap.

118
00:05:02,669 --> 00:05:04,101
So paint some crap,
and we can sell it.

119
00:05:04,103 --> 00:05:07,138
- Wait. You're not painting?
- No. I'm management.

120
00:05:07,140 --> 00:05:08,806
You two paint the stuff.
I'll do the rest.

121
00:05:08,808 --> 00:05:12,810
I'll be wheelin' and dealin'.
I'll be gettin' my percent.

122
00:05:13,712 --> 00:05:15,613
Okay, let's see
what you got so far.

123
00:05:15,615 --> 00:05:17,848
Time's up.
Paint brushes down.

124
00:05:17,850 --> 00:05:19,350
What the hell is this?

125
00:05:19,352 --> 00:05:22,687
I told you to paint
commercial, touristy crap.

126
00:05:22,689 --> 00:05:24,455
I'm sorry.
I'm not a sellout.

127
00:05:24,457 --> 00:05:25,923
I can only paint
what I feel.

128
00:05:25,925 --> 00:05:27,958
And I can only paint
the truth!

129
00:05:27,960 --> 00:05:29,393
The robots are coming!

130
00:05:29,395 --> 00:05:31,362
[ Imitating Laser Blasts ]

131
00:05:31,364 --> 00:05:32,396
Hide!

132
00:05:32,398 --> 00:05:33,431
Ah, this is great.

133
00:05:33,433 --> 00:05:35,700
You guys want to be
real artists, huh?

134
00:05:35,702 --> 00:05:37,802
Okay, that's an angle.
I can sell that.

135
00:05:37,804 --> 00:05:41,772
But if you're going artsy,
then you're going all the way.

136
00:05:41,774 --> 00:05:44,041
Someone's cutting off an ear.

137
00:05:44,043 --> 00:05:46,444
I need both of mine.
I wear glasses.

138
00:05:46,446 --> 00:05:47,678
Whelp, what's your excuse?

139
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:48,846
Don't got one.
Have at it.

140
00:05:48,848 --> 00:05:51,015
Teddy, what's wrong?
You haven't touched
your food.

141
00:05:51,017 --> 00:05:53,150
I don't know, Bob.
It's just the, uh--

142
00:05:53,152 --> 00:05:55,386
The anuses?
Yeah, you know.

143
00:05:55,388 --> 00:05:57,021
Yeah, they're, uh--
I know.

144
00:05:57,023 --> 00:05:58,522
They're like
Mona Lisa's eyes.

145
00:05:58,524 --> 00:06:00,124
They follow you
wherever you go.

146
00:06:00,126 --> 00:06:02,927
Ooh, you're right.
Well, I like 'em.

147
00:06:02,929 --> 00:06:04,128
You like 'em?
[ Groans ]

148
00:06:04,130 --> 00:06:05,129
Yeah. What's the problem?

149
00:06:05,131 --> 00:06:06,897
[ Bell Rings ]
The anus is
the window of the butt.

150
00:06:06,899 --> 00:06:09,567
It's true.
I guess she's just painting
what we're all thinking.

151
00:06:09,569 --> 00:06:12,570
Well, okay, but, Mort,
would you hang them up
in your funeral home?

152
00:06:12,572 --> 00:06:16,006
Course not. That would
be terrible for business.
I'm not an idiot.

153
00:06:16,008 --> 00:06:17,875
Count to three,
but do it on "two."

154
00:06:17,877 --> 00:06:21,445
I'll keep it on ice
until Art Crawl's over.
Thanks, T.

155
00:06:21,447 --> 00:06:22,546
Here goes.
Now listen, Gene.

156
00:06:22,548 --> 00:06:25,983
I'm gonna have trouble cutting
through the cartilage at first.
Mm-hmm.

157
00:06:25,985 --> 00:06:30,054
Uh! Aaah!
While I'm doing it,
just think about your art.

158
00:06:30,056 --> 00:06:30,821
Okay!
All right.

159
00:06:30,823 --> 00:06:33,824
Ready?
Ninja robot. Ninja robot.
Ninja robot.

160
00:06:33,826 --> 00:06:35,793
One, two--
Hey, kids.

161
00:06:35,795 --> 00:06:39,096
Oh, hey, Dad.
I had to get away from
those anuses for a while.

162
00:06:39,098 --> 00:06:41,499
- You mean Mort and Teddy?
- No. No.

163
00:06:41,501 --> 00:06:43,801
Your-- Gayle's paintings.
What are you kids doing?

164
00:06:43,803 --> 00:06:45,536
What knife?
What do you mean,
"What knife?"

165
00:06:45,538 --> 00:06:47,204
Why are you
holding a knife?
Why am I holding a knife?

166
00:06:47,206 --> 00:06:49,140
She's turning me
into a real artist.

167
00:06:49,142 --> 00:06:50,841
No, she's not.
Put the knife down.

168
00:06:50,843 --> 00:06:54,712
I want to be an artist!
Like Leonardo DiCaprio.

169
00:06:54,714 --> 00:06:55,679
That's right.

170
00:06:55,681 --> 00:06:56,847
That's da Vinci,
Gene.
No!

171
00:06:56,849 --> 00:07:00,818
The only way
I can sell this garbage
is if I make them legit!

172
00:07:00,820 --> 00:07:02,953
Hey, wait a second.
I have an idea.

173
00:07:02,955 --> 00:07:05,122
You know who loves
the stuff you kids draw?

174
00:07:05,124 --> 00:07:06,490
You?
No. Your mother.

175
00:07:06,492 --> 00:07:09,460
This crap is like catnip to her.
She can't resist it.

176
00:07:09,462 --> 00:07:10,094
Bring 'em inside.

177
00:07:10,096 --> 00:07:12,630
All right, we need to get
these up before they get back.

178
00:07:12,632 --> 00:07:14,799
Your mom will be so excited
to see this stuff...

179
00:07:14,801 --> 00:07:17,802
she won't even notice
that I took Gayle's
paintings down.

180
00:07:17,804 --> 00:07:20,838
Pretty manipulative, Dad.
I see where I get it.

181
00:07:20,840 --> 00:07:23,040
Thank you.
You should see my taxes.

182
00:07:23,042 --> 00:07:23,974
What's this supposed to be?

183
00:07:23,976 --> 00:07:26,911
A ninja robot fighting
a vampire tape recorder
at Stonehenge.

184
00:07:26,913 --> 00:07:29,613
- Who's that in the background?
- That's my friend Ken.

185
00:07:29,615 --> 00:07:32,116
Why is he like that?
He's an albino.

186
00:07:32,118 --> 00:07:32,850
Oh.
Yeah.

187
00:07:32,852 --> 00:07:34,952
I've never met Ken.
Is he real or imaginary?

188
00:07:34,954 --> 00:07:37,154
He's real, and he does
improvised hip-hop.

189
00:07:37,156 --> 00:07:38,889
Okay. How old is he?
He's 28.

190
00:07:38,891 --> 00:07:41,725
You can't have
a 28-year-old albino friend.

191
00:07:41,727 --> 00:07:42,526
Yes, I can!

192
00:07:42,528 --> 00:07:44,161
I can't deal with this
right now.

193
00:07:44,163 --> 00:07:46,597
- Tina, what do you got?
- It's our dentist.

194
00:07:46,599 --> 00:07:47,832
Dr. Yap?
Why is he nude?

195
00:07:47,834 --> 00:07:49,633
Wait. Has he been nude
with you, Tina?

196
00:07:49,635 --> 00:07:52,036
I exercised
some artistic license.

197
00:07:52,038 --> 00:07:52,770
[ Murmurs ]

198
00:07:52,772 --> 00:07:54,538
- We're switching dentists.
- No!

199
00:07:54,540 --> 00:07:55,973
I can't deal with that
right now.

200
00:07:55,975 --> 00:07:57,808
- But--
- Let's get 'em up.

201
00:07:57,810 --> 00:07:58,976
[ Bell Rings ]

202
00:07:58,978 --> 00:08:01,045
Linda, Gayle.
How was lunch?

203
00:08:01,047 --> 00:08:02,213
Very interesting.

204
00:08:02,215 --> 00:08:06,550
I think the waiter
might have been
hitting on me.

205
00:08:06,552 --> 00:08:09,253
Yes. He was
very attentive.

206
00:08:09,255 --> 00:08:11,255
And he asked you a lot
of questions about food.

207
00:08:11,257 --> 00:08:12,890
What was that all about?

208
00:08:12,892 --> 00:08:14,024
Uh, Bob?

209
00:08:14,026 --> 00:08:15,826
Where are my paintings?

210
00:08:15,828 --> 00:08:16,527
What? Wha-- Oh.

211
00:08:16,529 --> 00:08:20,564
I had to take a few down
to make room
for the kids' stuff.

212
00:08:20,566 --> 00:08:21,165
Bobby! Aw.

213
00:08:21,167 --> 00:08:22,633
- The kids' stuff!
- Yeah.

214
00:08:22,635 --> 00:08:25,736
It's like our wall
is a giant refrigerator.
I love it.

215
00:08:25,738 --> 00:08:28,105
Oh! Gee, Bob, if I didn't
know any better,

216
00:08:28,107 --> 00:08:31,108
I'd think you didn't
like my paintings.

217
00:08:31,110 --> 00:08:32,676
What? No. I--
Aw.

218
00:08:32,678 --> 00:08:35,179
No, no, no. I know when
I'm being lied to, Bob.

219
00:08:35,181 --> 00:08:40,684
It's like when I look at myself
in the mirror and say,
"It's going to be okay."

220
00:08:40,686 --> 00:08:43,020
Fine, look, Gayle,
I'm gonna level
with you.

221
00:08:43,022 --> 00:08:45,189
No. No, Bob.
No. No leveling.

222
00:08:45,191 --> 00:08:46,190
- No.
- Here we go.

223
00:08:46,192 --> 00:08:48,158
Gayle, the thing about
your paintings--

224
00:08:48,160 --> 00:08:49,760
Bobby!
[ Bell Rings ]

225
00:08:49,762 --> 00:08:52,296
Oh, look.
Senior visitors! Yay!

226
00:08:52,298 --> 00:08:55,165
Oh-ho-ho!
Well, look who it is.

227
00:08:55,167 --> 00:08:56,867
Great.
The art store people.

228
00:08:56,869 --> 00:09:01,038
Oh! Reflections.
I love that store!

229
